    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nUsing `vim.opt.foldexpr = \"v:lua.vim.treesitter.foldexpr()\"` while triggering some kind of autocompletion on insert mode and then going to normal mode without closing the autocompletion menu causes the following error:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nSe ha detectado un error al procesar InsertLeave Auto-Ã³rdenes para \"<buffer=1>\":\r\nError executing lua callback: ...s\\Neovim\\share\\nvim\\runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/_fold.lua:285: attempt to index field 'foldupdate_range' (a nil value)\r\nstack traceback:\r\n        ...s\\Neovim\\share\\nvim\\runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/_fold.lua:285: in function 'do_foldupdate'\r\n        ...s\\Neovim\\share\\nvim\\runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/_fold.lua:274: in function <...s\\Neovim\\share\\nvim\\runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/_fold.lua:273>\r\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim -u minimal.lua minimal.lua`\r\n2. `G` go to last line, `o` insert new line under current line and enter insert mode\r\n3. `local function something() end`\r\n4. Without closing the `pummenu`, `<esc>` go to normal mode\r\n5. The error is shown\r\n\r\nminimal.lua:\r\n```lua\r\nfunction ExampleOmnifunc(find_start, base)\r\n\tif find_start == 1 then\r\n\t\treturn #vim.api.nvim_get_current_line()\r\n\telseif find_start == 0 then\r\n\t\treturn { \"end\" }\r\n\tend\r\nend\r\n\r\nvim.opt.omnifunc = \"v:lua.ExampleOmnifunc\"\r\n\r\nvim.opt.foldenable = true\r\nvim.opt.completeopt = { \"menuone\", \"noselect\", \"noinsert\" }\r\nvim.opt.foldcolumn = \"1\"\r\nvim.o.foldlevelstart = 99\r\nvim.o.foldmethod = \"expr\"\r\nvim.opt.foldexpr = \"v:lua.vim.treesitter.foldexpr()\"\r\n\r\nlocal triggers = { \"d\" }\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"InsertCharPre\", {\r\n\tbuffer = vim.api.nvim_get_current_buf(),\r\n\tcallback = function()\r\n\t\tif vim.fn.pumvisible() == 1 or vim.fn.state(\"m\") == \"m\" then\r\n\t\t\treturn\r\n\t\tend\r\n\t\tlocal char = vim.v.char\r\n\t\tif vim.list_contains(triggers, char) then\r\n\t\t\tlocal key = vim.keycode(\"<C-x><C-o>\")\r\n\t\t\tvim.api.nvim_feedkeys(key, \"m\", false)\r\n\t\tend\r\n\tend,\r\n})\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThere should be no errors and folds should work as expected\r\n\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-2999+g38b9c322c\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nDoesn't apply\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 11 Pro 23H2\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nDoesn't apply\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nDoesn't apply\n\n### Installation\n\nnvim-win64.msi from the github releases page",
